		"History": "Adopted in 2006, these closures are meant to protect rare and potentially vital marine habitats.  Council action: Amendment 78 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP, and Amendment 7 to the Scallop FMP.  Only 24 seamounts exist within the EEZ off Alaska.  Of these, 16 are within the depth range of managed and fished species.  This system of closures protects these 16 seamounts as Habitat Areas of Particular Concern under the Magnuson-Stevens Act, the nation's primary framework for fishery management.  While they are relatively poorly understood, the 2006 Environmental Assessment of the amendments in question notes that these seamounts may harbor unique benthic ecosystems, serve as rearing habitats for many juvenile organisms, and provide feeding grounds for migratory species.  The analysis characterizes them as \"biological islands in the deep sea.\"",

		
