		"History": "The Bering Sea subarea was first closed to Atka mackerel fishing in 2010, with modifications enacted in 2014, to prevent fishing-related depletion of Steller sea lion prey.  Council action: 2010 interim final rule and 2014 final rule implementing Steller sea lion protection measures. Numerous measures have since been enacted to minimize fishery harvest of sea lion prey species, including the prohibition in 2010 of all Atka mackerel fishing in the Bering Sea subarea.  Following the 2014 NMFS Biological Opinion, this prohibition was altered by combining Aleutian Islands (AI) Area 541 with the Bering Sea subarea to shift effort into the Bering Sea and away from the numerous critical habitat areas of the AI region.",

		
