		"History": "Adopted in 2006, these closed areas were designed to protect corals and important rockfish habitat.  Council action: Amendment 78 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP, and Amendment 7 to the Scallop FMP.  The Council closed these waters as Essential Fish Habitat for a variety of rockfish.  The proposed rule notes that the Council selected areas \"on the upper to intermediate slope [...] based on the likely occurance of high relief corals and rockfish.\"  The Council sought to balance concerns regarding small fishing operations, noting in the final rule that \"almost 300 small entities may have operated in proximity to these areas from 1995-2003.\"  However, economic risk was determined to be only \"about 0.03 percent of total groundfish revenue for the affected vessels.\"",

		
