		"Area": "11,270",
		

		"History": "Implemented in 2010, this zone was intended to minimize damage to benthic habitats while facilitating continued flatfish harvest in the face of changing stock distribution.  Council action: Amendment 94 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP.  The proposed rule characterized this zone as necessary to \"reduce potential adverse effects of nonpelagic trawl gear on bottom habitat\" while \"allow[ing] for efficient flatfish harvest as the distribution of flatfish in the Bering Sea changes.\"  Amendment 94 altered the boundaries of the Northern Bering Sea Research Area to establish this zone, where groundfish bottom trawling using modified gear is allowed.  The amendment details specific gear-design requirements that greatly reduce trawl contact with the sea floor.  Public comment on the final rule was divided, with some lauding the action as wise management and others arguing that it revealed a lack of environmental concern.",

		
		"References": "<strong>Proposed rule on Amendment 94:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/75fr41123.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/75fr41123.pdf</a></br><strong>Final rule implementing Amendment 94:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/finalrules/75fr61642.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/finalrules/75fr61642.pdf</a></br><strong>Map of closed area:</strong></br>Located on page 37.</br><a href=\"https://www.afsc.noaa.gov/education/activities/PDFs/SBSS_Lesson6_BSAI_FMP.pdf\">https://www.afsc.noaa.gov/education/activities/PDFs/SBSS_Lesson6_BSAI_FMP.pdf</a>"
