		"Drivers": "habitat protection, climate change response, community impacts",
		
		"Area": "33,534",
		

		"History": "Implemented in 2008, this closure was designed to prevent adverse effects from bottom trawling on benthic habitats.  Council action: Amendment 89 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP.  The Council worked with a group of fishing industry and subsistence representatives to define this closed area.  This group identified bottom habitat that supports \"subsistence marine resources,\" including \"marine mammals, fish, and seabirds harvested by subsistence users from coastal and interior Alaska.\"  The final rule noted that Amendment 89 closures included such areas that support crucial subsistence resources, provide blue king crab habitat, and had not been subject to bottom trawling.  The rule also summarized multiple public comments supporting the closure as a means of precautionary management in the face of potential fishery effort shifts driven by climate change.",

		
