		"Drivers": "habitat protection, climate change response, community impacts",
		
		"Area": "24,416",
		

		"History": "Instituted in 2008, this closure was established to prevent damage to benthic habitats from bottom trawling.  Council action: Amendment 89 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP.  Concerns over habitat loss and social impacts, particularly as fish stocks shift northward, prompted this closure.  The proposed rule highlighted concerns regarding trawl \"interactions with community use and subsistence fisheries,\" as well as the importance of the area as blue king crab habitat.  The final rule explained that Amendment 89, which instituted multiple closures including this one, closed some areas that had never experienced bottom trawling, including habitat for blue king crab and other important subsistence species.  The rule also highlighted multiple public comments lauding the closures as effective examples of precautionary management.",

		
		"References": "<strong>Proposed rule on Amendment 89:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/73fr12357.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/73fr12357.pdf</a></br><strong>Final rule implementing Amendment 89:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/finalrules/73fr43362.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/finalrules/73fr43362.pdf</a></br><strong>Amendment 89 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/language.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/language.pdf</a></br><strong>Map of closed area:</strong></br>Located on page 5.</br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/language.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/language.pdf</a>"
