		"Area": "14,097",
		

		"History": "This area was closed in 2008 to protect sensitive habitat, particularly for blue king crab.  Council action: Amendments 89 and 94 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP.  One important driver for this closure was concern over the Pribilof Islands blue king crab stock, which was called \"severely depleted\" in NOAA's Environmental Assessment for Amendment 89.  It was feared that northward movement of flatfish stocks could bring bottom trawling to the area.  The final rule on Amendment 89 indicated that the Council worked \"in consultation with members of the nonpelagic trawl [fleet]\" to minimize any impacts on revenue.  The area was expanded in 2010 under Amendment 94 to \"protect additional blue king crab habitat\" according to the final rule for that action.",

		
		"References": "<strong>Proposed rule on Amendment 89:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/73fr12357.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/73fr12357.pdf</a></br><strong>Final rule implementing Amendment 89:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/finalrules/73fr43362.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/finalrules/73fr43362.pdf</a></br><strong>Amendment 89 to the BSAI Groundfish FMP:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/language.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/language.pdf</a></br><strong>Environmental Assessment, Regulatory Impact Review, and Initial Regulatory Flexibility Analysis for Amendment 89:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/analyses/earirfrfa_0508.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/analyses/earirfrfa_0508.pdf</a></br><strong>Proposed rule on Amendment 94:</strong></br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/75fr41123.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/75fr41123.pdf</a></br><strong>Final rule implementing Amendment 94:</strong></br><a href=\"http://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/frules/75fr61642.pdf\">http://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/frules/75fr61642.pdf</a></br><strong>Map of closed area:</strong></br>Located on page 30.</br><a href=\"https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/analyses/earirfrfa_0508.pdf\">https://alaskafisheries.noaa.gov/sites/default/files/analyses/earirfrfa_0508.pdf</a>"
